			[ Release notes ]



Old     version:  1.07  (01/09/2007)
Current version:  1.08  (25/09/2007)


SubVersion (CVS) revision: $Id$

TiLP is available for 4 platforms:
Linux (GTK/X11), Windows (GTK/GDI), Mac OS-X (GTK/X11) and FreeBSD (GTK/X11).


New capabilities:
-----------------

	- screenshot can be copied to clipboard
	

Improvements:
-------------

	- don't break USB communication if ROM dumping has been canceled
	- USB communication is more reliable (LPG's driver replaced by generic libusb-win32 one)


Bug fixes:
----------

	- full screen copy with Titanium hand-held
	- displaying of full path with Titanium/USB hand-held
	- sending of FLASH apps on TI73 hand-held
	- sending of FLASH apps on non-SE hand-helds (bug introduced in revision 3291)
	- progress bar update for backup & tigroup receiving
	- some Titanium/USB transfers can fail (when variable has an odd size)
	- added file extension for GRP variables


Known bugs:
-----------

	- the transfer dialog box is not always refreshed
	- [linux] Titanium DirectLink support works but:
		* w/ libusb: you will have to replug link cable whenever you exit TiLP
		* w/ kernel module: you don't have the issue stated below but replugging is
		  needed after module removal


Bug report:
-----------

If you think that you have found a bug, please report it. This allows us to 
improve TiLP and make it better.


Mailing:
--------

See the User's Manual...

The TiLP project by the TiLP team <http://lpg.ticalc.org/prj_tilp>.


Getting involved ?:
-------------------

See the Jobs section of the TiLP web site.